SIMPLE: integral
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Integral
<hw>In"te*gral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>int⟦eacute⟧gral</ets>. See <er>Integer</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Lacking nothing of completeness; complete; perfect;
uninjured; whole; entire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A local motion keepeth bodies <qex>integral</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Essential to completeness; constituent, as a part;
pertaining to, or serving to form, an integer; integrant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ceasing to do evil, and doing good, are the two great
<qex>integral</qex> parts that complete this duty.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Of, pertaining to,
or being, a whole number or undivided quantity; not fractional.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>Pertaining to, or proceeding by, integration; <as>as,
the <ex>integral</ex> calculus</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Integral calculus</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Calculus</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Integral</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Integral
<hw>In"te*gral</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A whole; an entire
thing; a whole number; an individual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>An expression which, being
differentiated, will produce a given differential. See differential
<er>Differential</er>, and <er>Integration</er>. Cf.
<er>Fluent</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Elliptic integral</b></col>, <cd>one of an important
class of integrals, occurring in the higher mathematics; -- so called
because one of the integrals expresses the length of an arc of an
<xex>ellipse</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Integrality</ent>⟦br⟧
